### Pulse API smoke test
### 1. Start the stack:  aspire start
### 2. Set @api to the apiservice URL and @anonKey to the anon key — both shown on the Aspire dashboard.
### 3. Run top to bottom (VS Code REST Client / Rider / VS).

@api = http://localhost:5000
@supabase = http://localhost:8000
@anonKey = <anon key from Aspire dashboard (supabase resource)>

### Sign in as Dom (pre-registered dev user)
# @name domLogin
POST {{supabase}}/auth/v1/token?grant_type=password
apikey: {{anonKey}}
Content-Type: application/json

{ "email": "dom@pulse.dev", "password": "Pulse123!" }

@domToken = {{domLogin.response.body.access_token}}

### Register this device for push (also provisions the user row on first authenticated call)
PUT {{api}}/api/devices
Authorization: Bearer {{domToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "fcmToken": "test-fcm-token-abc123",
  "platform": "Ios",
  "deviceModel": "iPhone 17 Pro",
  "deviceName": "Dom iPhone",
  "osVersion": "19.5",
  "appVersion": "1.0.0"
}

### Unregister the device (sign-out)
DELETE {{api}}/api/devices/test-fcm-token-abc123
Authorization: Bearer {{domToken}}
